" Ruby
" Use v or # to get a variable interpolation (inside of a string)}
" ysiw#   Wrap the token under the cursor in #{}
" v...s#  Wrap the selection in #{}
let g:surround_113 = "#{\r}"   " v
let g:surround_35  = "#{\r}"   " #

